    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Haider In Their Future</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Molly Martin letter on Roger Cohen's April 30 article finds disturbing Austrian politician Jorg Haider's Tommy Hilfiger-esque appeal to country's youth</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Many eerie images shine through Roger Cohen's compelling article (April 30), including Jorg Haider's virtual retraction of previous apologies he has made for praising Nazi employment policies. What I found most troubling, however, was Haider's Tommy Hilfiger-esque appeal to Austria's youth -- the sound-bite MTV voter with an attention span of three minutes.''</p>
        <p>Molly Martin</p>
        <p>West Hollywood, Calif.</p>
      </block>
